<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5122.1.1>
    dc:creator "Cancello, Eliana M.", "Chiquetto-Machado, Pedro I.", "Morales, Adriana C." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision of Paraphasma Redtenbacher, 1906 (Phasmatodea, Pseudophasmatidae) based on phallic and external morphology" ;
    bibo:endPage "80" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2022-03-30" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5122" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399542>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399654>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399658>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399662>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399666>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399668>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399672>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399676> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399542>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution map of Paraphasma. Circles indicate records based on material examined; triangles indicate records from the literature (Stoll 1787; Serville 1839; Chopard 1911; Conle et al. 2011; Jourdan et al. 2014); stars indicate records of undetermined Paraphasma species based on Rehn (1906) and Piza (1939) (although these authors identified the specimens, the identifications are doubtful or insufficient)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399542/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399654>
    dc:description "FIGURE 43. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), male, holotype of junior synonym Phasma maculatum Gray, 1835" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399658>
    dc:description "FIGURE 44. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), male, specimen MZUSP 0546. A–C. Habitus, dorsal (A), lateral (B) and ventral (C) views. D. Anterior region of the body, dorsolateral view. Scale bars = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399658/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399662>
    dc:description "FIGURE 45. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), male terminalia. A–D. Terminalia in dorsal (A), lateral (B), ventral (C) and oblique caudal (D) views. E. Detail of the subgenital plate and cerci, ventrolateral view. F. Drawing of the vomer. Abbreviations: Ce, cerci; S8, sternite VIII; SPa, anterior region of the subgenital plate; SPp, posterior region of the subgenital plate; T8, T9, T10, tergites VIII, IX and X; TP, thorn pad. Arrowhead = lateral projection of the subgenital plate. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399666>
    dc:description "FIGURE 46. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), illustrations of the phallic organ. A. Dorsal view. B. Detail of the sclerite of the ventral lobe in dorsal view. C. Caudal view. D. Left view. E. Right view. Abbreviations: b, base; dl, dorsal lobe; dp, distal process of the dorsal sclerite; rbp, right basal pouch; vl, ventral lobe. Colors: light gray, membranous regions; red, dorsal sclerite; green, sclerite of the ventral lobe; blue, base apodemes. In D and E the final portion of the ejaculatory duct is represented by transparency with dotted lines. Images A, B, D and E adapted from Chiquetto-Machado & Cancello (2021: fig 4)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399668>
    dc:description "FIGURE 47. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), female. A–D. Specimen MZUSP 0150, habitus in dorsal (A), lateral (B) and ventral (C) views, and anterior region of the body in dorsolateral view (D). E–G. Terminalia, dorsal (E), ventral (F) and lateral (G) views. Abbreviations: Ce, cerci; PO, praeopercular organ; SP, subgenital plate; T8, T9, T10, tergites VIII, IX and X. Scale bars = 10 mm, unless otherwise indicated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399668/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399672>
    dc:description "FIGURE 48. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), egg. Dorsal (A), lateral (B) and anterodorsal (C) views.Abbreviations: Ca, capsule; Op, operculum; MP, micropylar plate. Arrow = median line. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399676>
    dc:description "FIGURE 49. Paraphasma umbretta (Lichtenstein, 1796), live male from Manaus (Amazonas, Brazil). Habitus (A) and anterior region of the body (B) in dorsolateral view. Images provided by Raphael Heleodoro." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

